[2] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

2 Mar 2015 Guinea: EXCLUSIVE - Guinea says Ebola patients sent home after botched blood tests
https://in.news.yahoo.com/exclusive-guinea-says-ebola-patients-sent-home-botched-175435547.html
[Errors occurred in 2 treatment centers. Involved at least 20 and up to 52 patients, at least 4-6 were Ebola-positive on re-testing. Positive patients were sent home; 2-3 of them later died from Ebola. Facilities involved were one run by the government and supported by Cuban medical staff and one run by Medecins Sans Frontieres. Errors occurred when staff placed blood samples in the wrong test tubes, damaging specimens. Mistake (wrong vial-top color) was not noticed by testing lab.]

4 Mar 2015 Guinea: Guinea bets on mining for post-Ebola recovery
http://www.mineweb.com/news-fast-news/guinea-bets-on-mining-for-post-ebola-recovery/
[The economy of Guinea (the world's top exporter of the aluminum ore bauxite, also producing diamonds and gold) is likely to suffer a USD 2 billion loss from the Ebola outbreak.]

4 Mar 2015 Liberia: Trickle of Liberian children returning to school reflects lingering Ebola fears
http://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/05/world/africa/trickle-of-liberian-children-returning-to-school-reflects-lingering-ebola-fears.html

2 Mar 2015 Liberia: Quarantined SD Cooper Hospital declared Ebola free
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503021206.html?viewall=1

2 Mar 2015 Liberia: MOH takes Ebola preventive measures at borders
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503031604.html?viewall=1
[Ministry of Health states the measures taken at the Sierra Leone, Guinea and Ivory Coast borders with Liberia include the placement of thermometers and buckets with chlorinated water for washing of hands.]

3 Mar 2015 Liberia: Risking repetition - are we ignoring Ebola's lessons?
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503031006.html
[At the European Commission Meeting in Brussels, the International Rescue Committee published a set of recommendations in response to the Ebola outbreak.]

3 Mar 2015: Liberia's leader calls for "Marshall Plan" to eradicate Ebola, rebuild economies
http://www.foxbusiness.com/markets/2015/03/03/liberia-leader-calls-for-marshall-plan-to-eradicate-ebola-rebuild-economies/

3 Mar 2015: North Korea lifts Ebola travel restrictions
http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2015/mar/3/north-korea-lifts-ebola-travel-restrictionictions/

2 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: parliament orders detention of Ebola coordinator
http://naija247news.com/2015/03/probe-sierra-leone-parliament-orders-detention-of-ebola-coordinator/

2 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: Parliamentary Accounts Committee commences 1st hearing on auditor general's report on Ebola funds
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503020675.html?viewall=1
[Meeting was packed with observers. Several questions were raised about dishonored and returned checks, among other key concerns highlighted in the auditor general's report.]

3 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: From self-quarantine, VP says "Let everybody do the same."
http://awoko.org/2015/03/02/sierra-leone-news-from-self-quarantine-vp-says-let-everybody-do-the-same/

3 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: Sickle cell mother survives Ebola
http://awoko.org/2015/03/02/sierra-leone-news-sickle-cell-mother-survives-ebola/

3 Mar 2015: Sierra Leone sacks National Security boss
http://www.premiumtimesng.com/foreign/177836-ebola-sierra-leone-sacks-national-security-boss.html
[Head of National Security was sacked after security agents seized 250 kg of controversial Ebola blood samples, bound for South Africa, at Lungi International Airport.]

3 Mar 2015: Sierra Leone's young community leaders are best weapon against Ebola
http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2015/mar/03/sierra-leones-young-community-leaders-best-weapon-against-ebola
["What has started to turn the tide is Sierra Leoneans mobilising as communities to stem the flood of new infections."]

Non-governmental organization
-----------------------------
2 Mar 2015: Case study -- Nebraska's Ebola isolation and decontamination approach
http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2015-03/ehs-csn030215.php
[Discussed are the discharge process for a patient treated for EVD, body removal for a patient with EVD, and environmental decontamination of isolation unit.]

3 Mar 2015: The next Ebola zone: report finds 28 high-risk countries
http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ebola-virus-outbreak/next-ebola-zone-report-finds-28-high-risk-countries-n316436
[Save the Children reports 28 countries -- including Somalia, Chad, Nigeria, Afghanistan, Haiti, Ethiopia, Central Africa Republic, Niger, and Mali -- have weaker health care systems than Sierra Leone. When all expenses were figured, the international effort to end the outbreak that hit Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone last year [2014] cost an estimated USD 4.3 billion. Building up those countries' health infrastructures would have cost about USD 1.58 billion, according to Save the Children.]

3 Mar 2015 USA: ACLU-NJ (American Civil Liberties Union of New Jersey) sues state health department over documents relating to Ebola quarantines
http://www.northjersey.com/news/aclu-nj-sues-state-health-department-over-documents-relating-to-ebola-quarantines-1.1281596
[Suit is over the health department's refusal to provide public records regarding the development and implementation of state policies on handling potential Ebola cases.]

3 Mar 2015: Fight against Ebola cost European Union USD 1.3 billion -- European Union chief
http://sputniknews.com/world/20150303/1019007385.html#ixzz3TLizH1vQ

3 Mar 2015: The Ebola virus disease -- everything you need to know
http://sputniknews.com/infographics/20141105/1014307525.html
[Large graphic image]

3 Mar 2015 Plan International CEO: EU should be aware of "secret societies" when fighting Ebola
http://www.euractiv.com/sections/development-policy/plan-international-ceo-eu-should-be-aware-secret-societies-when-fighting
[Secret societies are groups of which nearly 80-90 per cent of the society are members. There are codes of conduct and ritual practices. They believe in discipline and loyalty, so it is difficult to shift their attitude away from the things they have been doing for years, like the washing of the dead or re-using the water from the washing.]

3 Mar 2015: Bridal store visited by Ebola nurse for sale for USD 338 000 as business fails to bounce back from "stigma"
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2977327/Ohio-bridal-shop-linked-Ebola-survivor-sell-building.html#ixzz3TLx7UmSk

3 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: 5 top Ebola contractors in illegal deals
http://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2015/03/sierra-leone-five-top-ebola-contractors-in-illegal-deals.html

4 Mar 2015 UK: Fleet fundraisers pay tribute to husband and wife team killed by Ebola
http://www.gethampshire.co.uk/news/local-news/fleet-fundraisers-pay-tribute-husband-8769708
[The husband, a child protection officer, sought out orphans in need of help and monitored them after the charity reunited them with relatives. The couple died in Sierra Leone, leaving behind a 7 year old son and 7 month old daughter.]

4 Mar 2015 UK: foreign secretary on Ebola outbreak in Africa
http://www.eureporter.co/world/2015/03/04/uk-foreign-secretary-on-ebola-outbreak-in-africa/>
["Instead of trying to develop solutions from outside and then getting communities on board, we need to proceed in reverse order. That is because public trust and confidence are key to effective intervention."]

USA
---
4 Mar 2015 USA (Lousiana): Ebola scare prompts temporary lockdown at St Bernard Parish Hospital
http://www.nola.com/health/index.ssf/2015/03/ebola_st_bernard_parish_hospit.html
[A patient, having "virtually all of the signs and symptoms of Ebola" entered the emergency department at 8 pm. Hospital was locked down, patient was placed in an isolation and infection-control room. All emergency dept visitors and staff involved in patient's treatment were contained. At 8:50 pm, the State Department of Health and Hospitals, the CDC, and the facility's doctors confirmed patient did not have Ebola.]

4 Mar 2015 USA (New Jersey): Violating Ebola quarantine would be a crime under proposal by NJ lawmaker
http://www.nj.com/politics/index.ssf/2015/03/violating_quarantine_would_be_a_crime_under_propos.html
[Consequences range from up to 6 months imprisonment and a USD 1000 fine to 3-5 years imprisonment and up to USD 15 000 fine.]

4 Mar 2015 USA (Texas): hospital disputes some claims made in nurse's Ebola lawsuit
http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/04/us-health-ebola-texas-nurse-idUSKBN0M021Q20150304?rpc=401
[A spokesman for the hospital said it complied with government privacy regulations to determine what information to share publicly about nurse NP's condition, and she consented to its release. The lawsuit also questioned the testimony before Congress of the hospital group's chief medical officer, calling it full of "numerous patently false statements." The spokesman for the hospital said the testimony ..."was factual and accurate, and any implication to the contrary is both false and irresponsible."]

2 Mar 2015 USA (Texas): Dallas Nurse's lawsuit underscores our worst fears about Ebola missteps
http://dallasmorningviewsblog.dallasnews.com/2015/03/nina-phams-lawsuit-underscores-our-worst-fears-about-ebola-missteps.html/

