3 Mar 2015: Fighting Ebola requires a culture change in the west, as well as west Africa
http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/mar/03/ebola-culture-change-west-africa-communities
[Communities need to be at the forefront to eradicate Ebola.]

3 Mar 2015: Ebola death toll in West Africa "could be much higher than initial estimates."
http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2015/mar/03/ebola-death-toll-west-africa-could-be-much-higher-than-initial-estimates
[Brussels conference attended by 3 West African presidents who warned of funding shortfall in reaching zero-cases target and a death toll higher than 1st thought.]

3 Mar 2015: Ebola czar -- "This thing isn't over yet." And the next pandemic could be even worse.
http://www.vox.com/2015/3/3/8134789/ebola-czar-ron-klain
[Interview with Ron Klain, ex-Ebola czar]

3 Mar 2015: Key messages for safe school operations in countries with outbreaks of Ebola
http://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/Ebola-Safe-School-Messages-2015-FINAL.pdf

3 Mar 2015: Engaging the African diaspora community on the international Ebola response
https://blogs.state.gov/stories/2015/03/03/engaging-african-diaspora-community-international-ebola-response

4 Mar 2015 West Africa: More Ebola in Guinea, Sierra Leone last week, no Liberia cases - WHO
http://www.trust.org/item/20150304205019-mwqz1/
[Guinea and Sierra Leone reported 132 new confirmed cases of Ebola in the week to 1 Mar 2015, an increase of 34 over last week. Half of the 51 new infections in Guinea came from registered contacts of Ebola patients. Some cases were only identified after postmortem testing. Unsafe burials were 16 in Sierra Leone and 16 in Guinea.]

4 Mar 2015 West Africa: Maternal health: Ebola's lasting legacy
http://www.nature.com/news/maternal-health-ebola-s-lasting-legacy-1.17036
["One of the most devastating consequences of the Ebola outbreak will be its impact on maternal health."]

