Drugs, vaccinations, technology
-------------
2 Mar 20 15 West Africa: Ebola, the executive summary -- 2 Mar 2015
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503031329.html?viewall=1
[In Sierra Leone, 4 new cases of Ebola were recorded Sun [1 Mar 2015], following a new cluster of cases among fishermen in Aberdeen, Freetown. Because of Liberia's decrease in confirmed Ebola patients, other sites in Guinea and Sierra Leone may be considered for ZMapp trial.]

3 Mar 2015: Progress towards new Ebola vaccine
http://www.clinicalservicesjournal.com/Print.aspx?Story=14008
[The results from the Phase III clinical trials of the proposed new vaccine in the UK show that it does produce a response from the immune system. Trials in affected countries are now needed to see whether it is sufficient to protect against the disease.]

4 Mar 2015: New tool can help identify nations vulnerable to Ebola
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503041092.html?viewall=1
[Using a "hot zone" screening tool that evaluates a nation's strengths across a wide range of measures such as political strength and health care capabilities. Part of a suite of "proof-of-concept" tools developed to help policymakers prepare for and respond to health disasters, such as Ebola]

